Retrieve a list of user tags.

getTags.Rd

This function allows you to retrieve a list of the users tags.

getTags(user, name = NULL, count = 100)

Arguments

user

A labstep user object. Must contain an `api_key` field. Returned from `login` command
name

Optionally specify the name of tags to retrieve.
count

Max number of results to return. Defaults to 100.

Value

Returns a list of tags with matching names.

Examples

user <- login("demo@labstep.com","demopassword")
tags <- getTags(user)
print(tags)
